## Installation

### Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/password-generator-web-app.git

cd password-generator-web-app
```

### Run the Application

Since this is a client-side web application, no installation or build process is required.

Simply open the `index.html` file in any modern web browser.

Alternatively, use a local development server:

```bash
python -m http.server 8000
```

Then navigate to:

```text
http://localhost:8000
```

## Usage

### Step 1: Select Password Length

Choose the desired password length using the number input field.

### Step 2: Configure Character Types

Select one or more of the following options:

* Uppercase Letters
* Lowercase Letters
* Numbers
* Symbols

### Step 3: Generate Password

Click the **Create a Password** button.

### Step 4: Copy and Use

The generated password will appear instantly on the screen and can be copied for use in accounts or applications.

## Example Configuration

| Setting   | Value   |
| --------- | ------- |
| Length    | 12      |
| Uppercase | Enabled |
| Lowercase | Enabled |
| Numbers   | Enabled |
| Symbols   | Enabled |

Example Output:

```text
A8#kP2@mL7!q
```

## Security Considerations

This project performs password generation entirely within the user's browser.

* No passwords are stored.
* No passwords are transmitted over a network.
* No external services are used.
* All processing occurs locally on the client side.

## Limitations

* Uses JavaScript's built-in randomization functions.
* Does not currently guarantee at least one character from each selected category.
* No password strength meter is included.
* No clipboard copy functionality is implemented.

